Pemex Output May Reach 3 Million Barrels in 2015-2017

-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-04-29T22:08:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/pemex-output-may-reach-3-million-barrels-in-2015-2017-1-.html
Petroleos Mexicanos, the state-run
 oil company , may see production rise to 3 million barrels a day
in the period from 2015 to 2017,  Juan Jose Suarez Coppel , chief
executive officer said today.  Pemex, as the company is known, will cut losses in its
refinery business by about 8 billion pesos this year, Suarez
Coppel said at an event in Mexico City.  Pemex pumped 2.58 million barrels of oil a day during the
first 24 days of the month, according to preliminary output
figures published on the companyâ€™s website April 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
